    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "You can use the `sortBy` argument to pass a regular JS sort function to override the sorting behaviour.\r\n\r\n```js\r\nsearch.addWidget(\r\n  instantsearch.widgets.refinementList({\r\n    container: '#brand-list',\r\n    attributeName: 'brand',\r\n    sortBy({ name: a }, { name: b }) {\r\n      return a.localeCompare(b);\r\n    },\r\n  })\r\n);\r\n```\r\n\r\nhttps://codesandbox.io/s/713rl3zwzq\r\n\r\nSorting can also be done in `transformItems` if you so prefer.",
    "created_at": "2018-12-13T12:40:06Z",
    "html_url": "https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch/issues/1377#issuecomment-446954367",
